article.description: — Brandon Murray had 20 points and Georgetown beat Siena 75-68 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Georgetown wins 75-68 against Siena
article.story: WASHINGTON -- — Brandon Murray had 20 points and Georgetown beat Siena 75-68 on Wednesday night. Murray added six rebounds for the Hoyas (5-5). Amir "Primo" Spears added 18 points while going 7 of 11 and 3 of 5 from the free throw line, and eight assists. Jay Heath recorded 16 points and shot 7 for 16, including 1 for 6 from beyond the arc. The Saints (5-4) were led in scoring by Jackson Stormo, who finished with 21 points and seven rebounds. Andrew Platek and Javian McCollum each had 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
